<doc id="864588" wikidata="Q4886885" url="?curid=864588" title="Benbane Head">
<text>Benbane Head, or Benbane (), is the northernmost point of mainland Northern Ireland. It is in County Antrim, near the Giant&#x27;s Causeway, which lies between Causeway Head and Benbane Head. The nearest settlements are Bushmills and Portballintrae.

